{"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"User Token and JWT","modules":[{"name":"JivoSDK"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For security reasons, chat history by default has a temporary nature and gets killed when providing another credentials into "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo\/session","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/JVSessionController\/startUp(channelID:userToken:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", or by calling ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo\/session"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/JVSessionController\/shutDown()","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It means, for example, if your client logs-out and then logs-in again, you may see him as entirely new client."},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Even in case he uses the same login credentials, and even in case you provide the same user_token for him into SDK."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To keep chat history alive between login sessions, you have to generate JWT token and use it as user_token."},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"text":"Below, we explain how to do that.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"#1: Prepare secret","anchor":"1-Prepare-secret","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First, you need to create your global "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"secret"},{"text":" which you’ll use for generating JWT tokens.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"text":"Please create it accordingly to RFC 7519, with length of 256 bit.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Then, share this secret with us by sending it to ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"info@jivosite.com"},{"text":" from e-mail address of your account’s administrator,","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"text":"and tell us your Mobile SDK Channel ID so we can configure our JWT environment for you.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You may found this resource useful to generate, sign, and check JWT tokens: "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/jwt.io\/","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"tip","name":"Tip","type":"aside"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"#2: Generate token","anchor":"2-Generate-token"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"JWT tokens you will generate for your clients, must be:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"unique across your account","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"constant for individual client","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"encrypted using your ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"secret"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Minimal JWT payload must contain “id” field which acts like a client identifier, so here is example of such JWT payload:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["{","    \"id\": \"egor531@example.com\"","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finally, you should feed your JWT as userToken parameter into:"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo\/session"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/JVSessionController\/startUp(channelID:userToken:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For security reasons, you’d better generate JWT tokens on your back-end,"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"text":"rather than doing it directly in the mobile app (because your ","type":"text"},{"code":"secret","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" might be stolen)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"important"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Required for keeping chat history alive","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/common_user_token"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/jivosdk\/common_user_token"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]},{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/jivosdk\/common_user_token"]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Setup","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/common_channel_setup","doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/common_project_config"]}],"references":{"doc://org.cocoapods.JivoSDK/documentation/JivoSDK/Jivo":{"url":"\/documentation\/jivosdk\/jivo","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Jivo","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text"